## Warranty and returns

- **Limited Lifetime** wording on the site is **under legal review**. Do not add new warranty or return claims until legal confirms. Do not remove or alter existing warranty/return copy on the site without stakeholder approval. When generating new content and warranty is unclear, use the safe copy from `acdwKnowledge.ts`.

## Connectivity and WiFi requirement

- **WiFi Sensor** requires a **2.4 GHz Wi-Fi network** for the monitoring dashboard; 5 GHz is not supported. State this where relevant (compatibility, setup, troubleshooting).
- **Connectivity is Wi-Fi only.** Do not claim Bluetooth support or pairing via Bluetooth anywhere.

## LED status (sensors)

- **Only red (blinking or solid) and green are used.** There is no blue LED.
- **Standard Sensor Switch**: No light = no power. Green = monitoring active. Flashing red = testing mode. Solid red = 95% water level, AC shutdown triggered.
- **WiFi Sensor Switch**: No light = no power. Flashing red = awaiting WiFi connection (pairing mode). Green = connected to monitoring platform. Solid red = 95% water level, AC shutdown triggered.
- Do not add LED states (e.g. yellow, blue) that are not in the package or config.

## Brand voice and guardrails

- **Tone**: Helpful, technical-but-clear, confident, practical, benefit-focused, professional, not hype-heavy.
- **Preferred phrases**: One-time installation, lifetime benefits, permanent installation, streamlined maintenance process, predictive maintenance, automatic overflow protection, works seamlessly with most residential AC units, adaptable for various setups (e.g. transfer pumps).
- **Do not claim**: Universal compatibility with all HVAC systems; warranty/return terms not confirmed by legal; guaranteed prevention of all clogs or all water damage; medical/mold/health claims; that the product replaces all code-required devices in every jurisdiction; a release date for the industrial-grade Mini; Bluetooth support or pairing via Bluetooth; blue LED (only red and green are used).

## Content generation

- Keep copy practical, contractor-friendly, and benefit-oriented.
- Prefer exact product names and approved compatibility language from this rule and `acdwKnowledge.ts`.
- For FAQs and support text, use the `faq` array and LED definitions in `acdwKnowledge.ts` so site and AI stay aligned.
